Four people were killed and 8 others seriously injured after a public service vehicle rammed into a stationery truck at Sobea area along the Nakuru- Eldoret highway. The incident happened barely 2 days after 11 people died in another tragic accident at Kimende along the Nairobi -Nakuru highway. The driver  of the ill-fated vehicle which was travelling from Eldoret to Nakuru is said to have rammed into the rear of the truck which had stalled on the road  side after  developing  a mechanical problem. 